verbose_text: The rapid adsorption of AFPIII to the ice reduced the sensitivity of the TH to the cooling rate and could explain the small variations in the TH measurements obtained in the presence of the moderate AFPs, which contrasted with the large variations seen with hypAFPs, as reported by Scotter et al. [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: AFPIII to the ice reduced the sensitivity of the TH
